==[[Etymology]]==
Latin ''respublica'', ''res publica'', literally 'public affairs'.

==[[Noun]]==

#A state where sovereignty rests with the people or their representatives, rather than a monarch or emperor; a country with no monarchy.
#(''US'') A representative democracy.

